The paper deals with the performance of filter bank multicarrier (FBMC) in the context of massive multi-input multi-output (MIMO) systems, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the impact of channel correlations on the performance of FBMC, which is a topic of interest in the signal processing (cs.SI) and networking (cs.NI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a new filter design method for FBMC, which could be of interest to researchers in the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
